column5: Hi All. Heading down to Florida next week and i,m renting a boat from holiday park in the everglades.Going for large mouth but not sure of the structure to look for or what works down there.Any help would be great will post pics when I get back. Thanks.
From what I understand live shiners on ballon rigs.

http://www.evergladesholidaypark.com/fishing.html  With probably a limited amount of fishing time available? The wild shiners are probably your best bet for a big fish?  Weeds, reeds, and lilies near deeper water? You can also try 8-10 inch plastics worms with probably a 5/0 worm hook.
Fort Lauderdale. 1981. I'll never forget it.
IGFA. Head office.   Worth a look if your close.
